sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Browser
    participant View as search view (views.py)
    participant Registry as SEARCH_REGISTRY
    participant Helpers as search_models (utils)
    participant Manager as SearchableManager
    participant QuerySet as SearchableQuerySet
    participant DB as Database

    %% =========================
    %% SEARCH REQUEST FLOW
    %% =========================
    User ->> Browser: Enter query
    Browser ->> View: GET /search/?q=...

    View ->> Registry: Read registered models
    Registry -->> View: List of searchable models

    View ->> Helpers: search_models(query, models)

    loop For each model
        Helpers ->> Manager: search(query_text)
        Manager ->> QuerySet: build queryset with snippets
        QuerySet ->> DB: Full-text search (tsvector/tsquery)
        DB -->> QuerySet: Matching rows
        QuerySet -->> Helpers: Annotated results
    end

    Helpers -->> View: Aggregated and grouped results
    View -->> Browser: Render template
    Browser -->> User: Display results

    %% =========================
    %% SIGNAL-BASED INDEXING
    %% =========================
    participant Signals as post_save signal

    Note over Signals: Triggered whenever a searchable model is saved

    Signals ->> DB: Update search_dict, tsv, simple_tsv
    DB -->> Signals: Indexed data stored

    %% =========================
    %% BACKFILL MANAGEMENT COMMAND
    %% =========================
    participant Command as backfill_searchable_models

    Note over Command: Runs manually via Django management command

    Command ->> DB: Fetch all model instances
    loop For each instance
        Command ->> DB: Save instance (triggers update)
        DB ->> Signals: post_save signal emitted
        Signals ->> DB: Recompute search_dict and vectors
    end